HEADWORD: Haematoxylin
<hw>Haem`a*tox"y*lin</hw> <pr>(-t⟦ocr⟧ks"⟦icr⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Haematoxylon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The coloring principle of logwood. It is obtained as a yellow
crystalline substance, <chform>C16H14O6</chform>, with a sweetish taste.
Formerly called also <altname>hematin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

